5000|$|The poet Pindar {{refers to}} the [...] "hounds of Geryon" [...] {{trembling}} before Heracles. Pindar's use of the plural [...] "hounds" [...] in connection with <b>Geryon</b> is unique. He may have used the plural because Orthus had multiple heads, or perhaps because he knew a tradition in which <b>Geryon</b> {{had more than one}} dog.|$|R
