50|$|The {{earliest}} {{depiction of}} Orthrus is {{found on a}} late seventh-century bronze horse pectoral from Samos (Samos B2518). It shows a two-headed Orthrus, with an arrow protruding {{from one of his}} heads, crouching at the feet, and in front of <b>Geryon.</b> Orthrus is facing Heracles, who stands to the left, wearing his characteristic lion-skin, fighting <b>Geryon</b> to the right.|$|R
